<subSubSection id="C37A6532FFD6FFDDFF78FE6C88DCFDD0" pageId="3" pageNumber="283" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDF36B9FFD6FFDDFF78FE6C88DCFDD0" blockId="3.[151,1436,258,610]" pageId="3" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis id="B914EAABFFD6FFDDFF78FE6C8D3EFE19" bold="true" box="[199,321,402,427]" pageId="3" pageNumber="283">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species can be differentiated from all known species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D3AFFD6FFDDFBEAFE6C88ADFE19" box="[1109,1234,402,427]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Xyphosiini">Xyphosiini</taxonomicName>
in having banded wing pattern and aculeus tip with preapical steps. Because of the yellow body and brown banded wing pattern 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D3AFFD6FFDDFF28FE248D4EFE41" box="[151,305,474,499]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Valera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aranai" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B914EAABFFD6FFDDFF28FE248D4EFE41" box="[151,305,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="283">Valera aranai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22757D0FFD6FFDDFE87FE258DC1FE41" box="[312,446,474,499]" pageId="3" pageNumber="283" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to species of Terellini with banded wings, but can be easily differentiated from them by having setulose frons and vein R 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD6FFDDFDDCFDF38E14FDA9" box="[611,619,525,539]" pageId="3" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD6FFDDFDCCFDF38E05FDA9" box="[627,634,525,539]" pageId="3" pageNumber="283" value="5.0">5</number>
, only yellow setae and setulae on body, and phallus glans with unpaired acrophallus and no sclerotised apicodorsal rod, as well as wing with M-shape pattern as on 
<figureCitation id="135B2A3CFFD6FFDDFB2DFDDB895DFD8C" box="[1170,1314,549,574]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1817,1840]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,703,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,662,1796]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Valera ariana, 1. Lateral habitus, Holotype, ♀. 2. Thorax. 3. Head in profile. 4. Wing, Paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267647/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="283">
Figs. 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD6FFDDFB6FFDD888A1FD8C" box="[1232,1246,550,574]" pageId="3" pageNumber="283" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD6FFDDFAABFDD8895DFD8C" box="[1300,1314,550,574]" pageId="3" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
(the discal and preapical crossbands connected at posterior margin), unknown for any terelliine species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
