<subSubSection id="C37A6532FFD0FFDBFF78FF698FE8FA40" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDF36B9FFD0FFDBFF78FF6989E2FE35" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B914EAABFFD0FFDBFF78FF698DD8FF02" bold="true" box="[199,423,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Description. 
<emphasis id="B914EAABFFD0FFDBFEDFFF698DD8FF02" bold="true" box="[352,423,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Head:</emphasis>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="135B2A3CFFD0FFDBFE08FF698D85FF02" box="[439,506,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1817,1840]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,703,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,662,1796]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Valera ariana, 1. Lateral habitus, Holotype, ♀. 2. Thorax. 3. Head in profile. 4. Wing, Paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267647/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFE53FF668D85FF02" box="[492,506,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) Head yellowish brown except ocellar triangle black; length: height: width ratio = 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFF28FF428CD8FF66" box="[151,167,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
: 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFF0BFF428C96FF66" box="[180,233,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.23">1.23</number>
: 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFF4CFF428D58FF67" box="[243,295,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.35">1.35</number>
. Frons 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFEC6FF428DB6FF67" box="[377,457,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.4" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.3">1.3-1.5</number>
times as wide as long. Frontal and orbital plates with yellowish setulae. Eye 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFA97FF428926FF67" box="[1320,1369,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.65">1.65</number>
times as high as long. Antenna yellow, scape with 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFD37FF1E8EB2FF4A" box="[648,717,224,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12</number>
dark brownish setulae at dorso-apical margin; first flagellomere 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFF28FEFA8CB7FEAF" box="[151,200,260,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.45">1.45</number>
times as long as wide and distinctly rounded apicodorsally; arista very short pubescent, yellow at base and brown in its slender part. Gena 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFE43FED98E52FEF2" box="[508,557,295,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="0.85">0.85</number>
times as high as first flagellomere and 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFC55FED68864FEF2" box="[1002,1051,296,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="0.33">0.33</number>
as high as eye. Proboscis capitate with yellowish brown setulae. Three frontal and two orbital setae present. All setae dark yellow and all setulae yellow except genal setulae anterior to genal seta short, brown. Palpus yellow, with sparse yellow and brown setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36B9FFD0FFDBFF78FE6A8883FD37" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B914EAABFFD0FFDBFF78FE6A8D5AFE1F" bold="true" box="[199,293,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Thorax:</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="135B2A3CFFD0FFDBFE87FE6A8D01FE1E" box="[312,382,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1817,1840]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,703,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,662,1796]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Valera ariana, 1. Lateral habitus, Holotype, ♀. 2. Thorax. 3. Head in profile. 4. Wing, Paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267647/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFED0FE6A8D01FE1E" box="[367,382,404,428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) Yellow in ground color. Scutum 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFCB2FE6A8F4FFE1E" box="[781,816,404,428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.2">1.2</number>
times as wide as long (between presutural supra-alar setae). In greasy specimens small round black presutural spots are visible near supra-alar setae and black vitta is present in the middle of scutum from anterior margin, extending posteriorly beyond transverse suture. The black pattern is obscured by yellow microtrichia in dry specimens. Pleuron yellow; only triangular mark on katepisternum reddish brown, obscured by yellow microtrichia; scutellum subshining yellow; slightly wider than long, with 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFEAFFDB98D29FDD2" box="[272,342,583,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="13.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="12.0">12–15</number>
white setulae on each margin. Scutellum slightly convex with 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFBA4FDB68856FDD2" box="[1051,1065,584,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="2.0">2</number>
pairs of setae (apical 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFA9EFDB6893BFDD2" box="[1313,1348,584,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="0.9">0.9</number>
as long as basal one). Subscutellum and mediotergite yellow. All setae on thorax dark yellow. Halter yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36B9FFD0FFDBFF78FD6E8F71FD7F" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B914EAABFFD0FFDBFF78FD6E8C82FD15" bold="true" box="[199,253,656,679]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Legs</emphasis>
: uniformly yellow, without modifications, not swollen; fore femur with 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFB8EFD6E8840FD1A" box="[1073,1087,656,680]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="2.0">2</number>
rows of posterodorsal and one row of posteroventral setae; all setae and setulae yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36B9FFD0FFDBFF78FD2989E2FBF2" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B914EAABFFD0FFDBFF78FD298D72FD42" bold="true" box="[199,269,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Wing:</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="135B2A3CFFD0FFDBFEA2FD298D1DFD42" box="[285,354,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1817,1840]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,703,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,662,1796]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Valera ariana, 1. Lateral habitus, Holotype, ♀. 2. Thorax. 3. Head in profile. 4. Wing, Paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267647/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFEEEFD268D1DFD42" box="[337,354,728,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hyaline with pattern of somewhat m-like appearance because of four well developed brownish crossbands. Base of wing, excluding (partly) distal half of cell c, cells bm and bcu and alula, yellowish brown. pterostigma entirely brown. Subbasal crossband reaching from pterostigma to vein A 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFB3AFCD088F2FC8E" box="[1157,1165,814,828]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
+Cu 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFB02FCD088BAFC8E" box="[1213,1221,814,828]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="2.0">2</number>
. Discal crossband complete, crossing wing from pterostigma through R-M crossvein, reaching posterior margin of the wing. Discal crossband fused with subbasal crossband in anterior margin (perostigma, cells r 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFB97FC87884FFC35" box="[1064,1072,889,903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
and r 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFBCBFC878803FC35" box="[1140,1148,889,903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFB3AFC8788F3FC35" box="[1157,1164,889,903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="3.0">3</number>
) of the wing. Preapical band complete, crossing wing from pterostigma through dm-cu crossvein, reaching posterior margin of the wing. Preapical and apical crossbands fused in cells r 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFD1DFC3A8ED5FC60" box="[674,682,964,978]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
and r 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFD57FC3A8E8FFC60" box="[744,752,964,978]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFD46FC3A8F7FFC60" box="[761,768,964,978]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="3.0">3</number>
; preapical and discal crossbands are converging and widely connected near posterior margin of wing, forming m-shape pattern. Brown spot present in the hyaline interspace between discal and preapical crossbands in cell r 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFD74FBF18EACFBAF" box="[715,723,1039,1053]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
(
<figureCitation id="135B2A3CFFD0FFDBFD5AFBFE8F56FBAB" box="[741,809,1024,1049]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1817,1840]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,703,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,662,1796]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Valera ariana, 1. Lateral habitus, Holotype, ♀. 2. Thorax. 3. Head in profile. 4. Wing, Paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267647/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFCA3FBFF8F56FBAB" box="[796,809,1025,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). In 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFCDAFBFF8F0CFBAB" box="[869,883,1025,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="3.0">3</number>
<typeStatus id="54DB881BFFD0FFDBFCC2FBFF8FA2FBAB" box="[893,989,1025,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">paratype</typeStatus>
males this spot merged with preapical crossband (
<figureCitation id="135B2A3CFFD0FFDBFEA9FBD98D24FB8D" box="[278,347,1063,1088]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1817,1840]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,703,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,662,1796]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Valera ariana, 1. Lateral habitus, Holotype, ♀. 2. Thorax. 3. Head in profile. 4. Wing, Paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267647/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFEF5FBD98D24FB8D" box="[330,347,1063,1087]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Setae on dorsal side of vein R 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFD03FBC88EBBFBF6" box="[700,708,1078,1092]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
without gap at Sc apex level. Vein R 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFBDFFBC88817FBF6" box="[1120,1128,1078,1092]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFBCEFBC88807FBF6" box="[1137,1144,1078,1092]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="5.0">5</number>
with 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFB08FBD9889EFBF2" box="[1207,1249,1063,1088]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
setulae dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36B9FFD0FFDBFF78FBB38D3DFB1C" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B914EAABFFD0FFDBFF78FBB38D41FBD4" box="[199,318,1101,1126]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B914EAABFFD0FFDBFF78FBB38D4AFBD4" bold="true" box="[199,309,1101,1126]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Abdomen</emphasis>
:
</emphasis>
General colour dark yellow; tergites without black spots, covered by white setulae; all setae yellow. Marginal setae on female tergites 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFDB0FB8C8E46FB39" box="[527,569,1138,1163]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
pale yellow; tergite 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFCA3FB8C8F55FB39" box="[796,810,1138,1163]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="5.0">5</number>
of male 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFC34FB8C8FD1FB38" box="[907,942,1138,1162]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="0.3">0.3</number>
times as long as abdomen and without spots on hindmargin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36B9FFD0FFDBFF78FB448E71FA8C" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B914EAABFFD0FFDBFF78FB448DF4FB60" box="[199,395,1210,1235]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B914EAABFFD0FFDBFF78FB448DFCFB61" bold="true" box="[199,387,1210,1235]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Male terminalia</emphasis>
:
</emphasis>
Epandrium oval in dorsal view, with posterior lobe of lateral surstylus well protruding and moderately setulose. surstylus with two prensisetae. lateral prensiseta much smaller than medial one (
<figureCitation id="135B2A3CFFD0FFDBFABDFB23893AFB44" box="[1282,1349,1245,1270]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[250,1383,245,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[214,1404,196,1880]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 10. Valera ariana, 5. Aculeus. 6. Aculeus apex. 7. Spermatheca. 8. Epandrium, posterior view. 9. Ejaculatory apodeme. 10. Glans of phallus, lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267648/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFA89FB20893AFB44" box="[1334,1349,1246,1270]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Glans of phallus as in 
<figureCitation id="135B2A3CFFD0FFDBFEF3FAFC8DE0FAA8" box="[332,415,1282,1307]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[250,1383,245,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[214,1404,196,1880]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 10. Valera ariana, 5. Aculeus. 6. Aculeus apex. 7. Spermatheca. 8. Epandrium, posterior view. 9. Ejaculatory apodeme. 10. Glans of phallus, lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267648/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFE3FFAFC8DE0FAA8" box="[384,415,1282,1306]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
; with wide tubular base of acrophallus and rather large and wide apical semitubular lobes. Ejaculatory apodeme as in 
<figureCitation id="135B2A3CFFD0FFDBFE79FADB8E75FA8C" box="[454,522,1317,1342]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[250,1383,245,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[214,1404,196,1880]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 10. Valera ariana, 5. Aculeus. 6. Aculeus apex. 7. Spermatheca. 8. Epandrium, posterior view. 9. Ejaculatory apodeme. 10. Glans of phallus, lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267648/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFE46FAD88E75FA8C" box="[505,522,1318,1342]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36B9FFD0FFDBFF78FAB48C8DFA18" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B914EAABFFD0FFDBFF78FAB48DD8FAD0" box="[199,423,1354,1379]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B914EAABFFD0FFDBFF78FAB48DE2FAD1" bold="true" box="[199,413,1354,1379]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Female terminalia</emphasis>
:
</emphasis>
Oviscape brown, about as long as preabdomen. Aculeus brown, length/width ratio = 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFAD4FAB489E3FAD1" box="[1387,1436,1354,1379]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="6.25">6.25</number>
(
<figureCitation id="135B2A3CFFD0FFDBFF20FA938C9CFA34" box="[159,227,1389,1414]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[250,1383,245,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[214,1404,196,1880]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 10. Valera ariana, 5. Aculeus. 6. Aculeus apex. 7. Spermatheca. 8. Epandrium, posterior view. 9. Ejaculatory apodeme. 10. Glans of phallus, lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267648/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFF6CFA938C9CFA34" box="[211,227,1389,1414]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aculeus tip blunt with pair of preapical steps (
<figureCitation id="135B2A3CFFD0FFDBFD43FA938F40FA34" box="[764,831,1389,1414]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[250,1383,245,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[214,1404,196,1880]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 10. Valera ariana, 5. Aculeus. 6. Aculeus apex. 7. Spermatheca. 8. Epandrium, posterior view. 9. Ejaculatory apodeme. 10. Glans of phallus, lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267648/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFC90FA938F40FA34" box="[815,831,1389,1414]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Two round densely and long papillose spermathecae (
<figureCitation id="135B2A3CFFD0FFDBFF20FA6C8C9BFA18" box="[159,228,1426,1451]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[250,1383,245,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[214,1404,196,1880]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 10. Valera ariana, 5. Aculeus. 6. Aculeus apex. 7. Spermatheca. 8. Epandrium, posterior view. 9. Ejaculatory apodeme. 10. Glans of phallus, lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267648/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA8249EFFD0FFDBFF6BFA6C8C9BFA18" box="[212,228,1426,1450]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36B9FFD0FFDBFF78FA4B8FE8FA40" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B914EAABFFD0FFDBFF78FA4B8D09FA7C" bold="true" box="[199,374,1461,1486]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Measurements</emphasis>
. Female. Body length 
<quantity id="4C989B5CFFD0FFDBFDC4FA488EACFA7C" box="[635,723,1462,1486]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="8.3">8.3 mm</quantity>
(including the oviscape), wing length 
<quantity id="4C989B5CFFD0FFDBFB34FA4B8899FA7C" box="[1163,1254,1461,1486]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="6.2">6.2 mm</quantity>
. Aculeus length 
<quantity id="4C989B5CFFD0FFDBFF28FA248C81FA40" box="[151,254,1498,1523]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="2.25">2.25 mm</quantity>
. Male. Body length 
<quantity id="4C989B5CFFD0FFDBFE5EFA248EFAFA40" box="[481,645,1498,1523]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.875" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="5.25" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="5.875" valueMax="6.5" valueMin="5.25">5.25—6.5 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity id="4C989B5CFFD0FFDBFCA2FA248FEDFA40" box="[797,914,1498,1523]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.85" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="5.85" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.7">5.7–6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37A6532FFD0FFDBFF78FA038D90F989" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDF36B9FFD0FFDBFF78FA038D90F989" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B914EAABFFD0FFDBFF78FA038D31F9A7" bold="true" box="[199,334,1533,1558]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named after Aria Mountain, near Kashmar (Khorasan Razavi Province), where the 
<typeStatus id="54DB881BFFD0FFDBFF7FF9DD8C8FF989" box="[192,240,1571,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">type</typeStatus>
species was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
